---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Blogs FastAPI"
  description="A production-grade blogging REST API backend built with FastAPI, featuring full CRUD, authentication, and a clean modular architecture deployed on Render."
  category="Backend · REST API"
  period="August 2025"
  githubUrl="https://github.com/srikar2908/Blogs_FastAPI"
  liveUrl="https://blogs-fastapi.onrender.com"
  techTags={["Python", "FastAPI", "PostgreSQL", "SQLAlchemy", "JWT", "Pydantic", "Alembic"]}
>
  <!-- Overview Section -->
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">Project Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      Blogs FastAPI is a production-ready, high-performance REST API backend designed for blogging platforms. It features secure JWT authentication, multi-model relational tables (Users, Posts, Comments), automated database migrations, and self-documenting endpoints.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      Developed using a modular router architecture, the project demonstrates software design patterns in API building with Python. It isolates routers, data models, schema definitions, and database helper files to create a scalable foundation for modern web clients.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem & Solution Section -->
  <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 pt-4">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">The Goal</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Establish a fast, standards-compliant REST backend that serves CRUD data securely. The design must handle token-based user verification, prevent cross-post modifications by unauthorized accounts, and document all available endpoints automatically.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">The Architecture</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        FastAPI serves as the core ASGI driver, routing client HTTP requests through JWT authentication middleware. Schema structures are validated using Pydantic, data transactions are managed using the SQLAlchemy ORM, and migrations are handled via Alembic.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Animated Architecture Diagram Section -->
  <section class="space-y-4 pt-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">System Dataflow</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      Request-response pipeline mapping how client payloads transit the backend modules.
    </p>
    
    <div class="glass-card p-6 md:p-8 flex items-center justify-center bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark overflow-x-auto">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 800 420" width="800" height="420" class="w-full max-w-[700px] text-foreground select-none">
        <style>
          @keyframes draw { to { stroke-dashoffset: 0; } }
          @keyframes fadeUp { to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }
          .node { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); animation: fadeUp 0.5s forwards cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1); }
          .arrow { stroke-dasharray: 100; stroke-dashoffset: 100; animation: draw 1.2s forwards ease-in-out; }
        </style>

        <!-- Column 1: Client -->
        <g class="node" style="animation-delay: 0s;">
          <rect x="20" y="160" width="130" height="60" rx="8" fill="rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05)" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="85" y="195" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="currentColor" text-anchor="middle">Client HTTP</text>
        </g>

        <!-- Arrow 1 to 2 -->
        <path d="M 150 190 L 210 190" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="arrow" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;"/>

        <!-- Column 2: Router Layer -->
        <g class="node" style="animation-delay: 0.4s;">
          <rect x="210" y="160" width="140" height="60" rx="8" fill="rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05)" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="280" y="190" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="11" font-weight="bold" fill="currentColor" text-anchor="middle">FastAPI Routers</text>
          <text x="280" y="205" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="hsl(var(--muted-foreground))" text-anchor="middle">Endpoint Resolvers</text>
        </g>

        <!-- Arrow 2 to 3 -->
        <path d="M 350 190 L 410 190" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="arrow" style="animation-delay: 0.6s;"/>

        <!-- Column 3: Middleware -->
        <g class="node" style="animation-delay: 0.8s;">
          <rect x="410" y="160" width="140" height="60" rx="8" fill="rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05)" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="480" y="190" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="11" font-weight="bold" fill="currentColor" text-anchor="middle">JWT Middleware</text>
          <text x="480" y="205" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="hsl(var(--muted-foreground))" text-anchor="middle">Auth & Verify Scope</text>
        </g>

        <!-- Arrow 3 to 4 -->
        <path d="M 550 190 L 610 190" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="arrow" style="animation-delay: 1.0s;"/>

        <!-- Column 4: ORM -->
        <g class="node" style="animation-delay: 1.2s;">
          <rect x="610" y="160" width="150" height="60" rx="8" fill="rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05)" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="685" y="190" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="11" font-weight="bold" fill="currentColor" text-anchor="middle">SQLAlchemy ORM</text>
          <text x="685" y="205" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="hsl(var(--muted-foreground))" text-anchor="middle">Model Mappings</text>
        </g>

        <!-- Arrow from ORM down to Database -->
        <path d="M 685 220 L 685 280" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="arrow" style="animation-delay: 1.4s;"/>

        <!-- Row Bottom: Postgres Database -->
        <g class="node" style="animation-delay: 1.6s;">
          <rect x="610" y="280" width="150" height="60" rx="8" fill="rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05)" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="685" y="315" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="currentColor" text-anchor="middle">PostgreSQL</text>
        </g>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interactive Swagger Mockup -->
  <section class="space-y-4 pt-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">Interactive OpenAPI Documentation</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      FastAPI automatically serves a Swagger UI client for real-time testing and endpoint auditing.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-border rounded-xl bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark overflow-hidden shadow-md">
      <div class="bg-secondary/50 border-b border-border px-4 py-2 flex items-center justify-between">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-red-400"></span>
          <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-yellow-400"></span>
          <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-green-400"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[10px] text-muted-foreground font-mono bg-background border border-border px-3 py-0.5 rounded select-none">
          https://blogs-fastapi.onrender.com/docs
        </div>
        <div class="w-10"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 bg-background text-left space-y-4">
        
        <!-- Swagger Header -->
        <div class="border-b border-border pb-4">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary font-heading">Blogs API</h4>
          <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground text-[10px] font-bold rounded">1.0.0</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground block mt-1">OpenAPI specifications generated by FastAPI schema engines.</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Endpoint Rows -->
        <div class="space-y-2.5 text-xs font-mono">
          <!-- POST User -->
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-2.5 bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/25 rounded-lg">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-600 text-white font-bold rounded text-[9px] uppercase tracking-wider">POST</span>
              <span class="font-bold text-primary">/users</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">Create User Profile</span>
          </div>

          <!-- POST Login -->
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-2.5 bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/25 rounded-lg">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-600 text-white font-bold rounded text-[9px] uppercase tracking-wider">POST</span>
              <span class="font-bold text-primary">/login</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">Authenticate & Retrieve JWT</span>
          </div>

          <!-- GET Posts -->
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-2.5 bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/25 rounded-lg">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold rounded text-[9px] uppercase tracking-wider">GET</span>
              <span class="font-bold text-primary">/posts</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">Fetch Paginated Blog Posts</span>
          </div>

          <!-- PUT Posts -->
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-2.5 bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/25 rounded-lg">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-yellow-600 text-white font-bold rounded text-[9px] uppercase tracking-wider">PUT</span>
              <span class="font-bold text-primary">/posts/&#123;id&#125;</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">Update Target Blog Post</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Features List -->
  <section class="space-y-4 pt-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">Key Features</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="border border-border p-4 rounded-xl bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark space-y-1.5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-sm text-primary">JWT Token Access Controls</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Verifies incoming user tokens and restricts write access to the original post author.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-border p-4 rounded-xl bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark space-y-1.5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-sm text-primary">SQLAlchemy Relational Models</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Configures post-to-comment foreign key relationships with cascading deletes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-border p-4 rounded-xl bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark space-y-1.5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-sm text-primary">Alembic Database Versioning</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Tracks database model modifications sequentially, managing schema updates.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-border p-4 rounded-xl bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark space-y-1.5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-sm text-primary">Pydantic Schemas</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Enforces input validation and serialization, outputting clear error arrays.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Technical Challenges Section -->
  <section class="space-y-4 pt-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">Technical Challenges & Decisions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-1">N+1 Query Resolution in SQLAlchemy</h4>
        <p>
          Fetching all posts alongside comments and author profiles was causing severe N+1 database queries. I resolved this by utilizing SQLAlchemy's joint-load options (<code>joinedload</code>) in DB queries, reducing transactions down to a single relational query.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-1">Password Encryption Standards</h4>
        <p>
          Ensuring secure credentials storage is critical. Passwords are encrypted at user creation using the <code>bcrypt</code> hashing algorithm, making it impossible to read user passwords from the relational databases.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Impact and Results -->
  <section class="space-y-4 pt-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">Project Impact</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2.5 list-none p-0 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-accent text-lg">⚡</span>
        <span><strong>Sub-50ms Response Times</strong> during high-load API endpoint benchmarks.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-accent text-lg">⚡</span>
        <span><strong>100% Type Validation:</strong> Pydantic handles validation, removing hand-crafted try-except loops.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-accent text-lg">⚡</span>
        <span><strong>Deployment Ready:</strong> Packaged and deployed to Render with zero environment dependency drift.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</ProjectLayout>
